tor-onions-server (0.7.0.4~trusty) trusty; urgency=medium

  * Refactored all communication to a pure request-response model.
  * Updated communications format.
  * Normal name servers pass Merkle root signatures to clients.
  * Sign all outbound communication using Ed25519 key.
  * Add Clang's scan-build static analysis tool to build scripts.
  * Install to /usr/local/ when compiled from source.
  * Many bug fixes.

 -- Jesse Victors <kernelcorn@riseup.net>  Mon, 28 Sep 2015 13:00:00 -0800

tor-onions-server (0.6.0.3~trusty) trusty; urgency=medium

  * Management of Ed25519 keypairs.
  * Support for hidden services as hosts. (#46, #71)
  * Improved distinction of roles between server types. (#69)
  * Several bugfix regarding message fragmentation. (#64, #68)
  * Automatic timestamped signing of Merkle tree root. (#50, #58)
  * Introduced Page data structure. (#18)

 -- Jesse Victors <kernelcorn@riseup.net>  Wed, 26 Aug 2015 23:00:00 -0800

tor-onions-server (0.5.0.1~trusty) trusty; urgency=medium

  * Reduced most compiler and static analysis warnings.
  * Added popt-dev as a missing dependency.
  * Updated network protocol.
  * Workaround for a communications issue. (#68)

 -- Jesse Victors <kernelcorn@riseup.net>  Fri, 07 Aug 2015 16:00:00 -0800

tor-onions-server (0.4.0.2~trusty) trusty; urgency=medium

  * Capability to bind to a specific IPv4 address.
  * Mirrors now attempt to reestablish a lost connection to a Quorum server.
  * Logging of all events to a file or to standard out.
  * Improved logging and diagnostic information.
  * Added identification numbers to the logs from each network session.
  * Introduced a flag to specify the log filepath.
  * Introduced onions-server manpage.
  * Fixed all servers being unable to send Records to subscribers.
  * Standardized the build process.
  * Improved git commit styles to match common standard.
  * Clarified README.
  * Many bug fixes.

 -- Jesse Victors <kernelcorn@riseup.net>  Tues, 04 Aug 2015 09:00:00 -0800

